###1. [INNX Stretchable Back Seat Barrier](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01M724OX6/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B01M724OX6&linkId=162b5b382e26bf90f211dd9a4366022a)

This is perfect for making sure my dog doesn't climb into the front seat of my car and claw up the center console.
It also prevents Viira from jumping in my lap while going 70 on the freeway, helping keep us both safe.

I've gone through several similar products that either didn't fit very well or did little to keep my dog out of the front seat.
This one works well and is easy to attach.
Additionally it is cheaper than most [metal](https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000I1PJNO/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&tag=bonktothefi07-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&linkCode=as2&creativeASIN=B000I1PJNO&linkId=b30e5b3f7c8f160ef357f8f0b53f4b68) alternatives.

